        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 3:28AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 328 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 15 miles southeast of Cloudy to near Blossom to
7 miles west of Lake Sulphur Springs. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Clarksville, Broken Bow, Idabel, Rufe, Hochatown, Woodland,
Redland, Hagansport, Wright City, Kanawha, Glover, Garvin, Bogata,
Kiomatia, Johntown, Oak Hill, Golden, Farmers Hill, and Millerton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
